  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of lifesaving and sustainable WASH services to drought affected populations in Northern Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to improve access to clean, safe, and appropriate water supply for vulnerable drought affected communities in Sool, Sanaag, and Nugal. IOM will use CERF funds to provide water vouchers, rehabilitate water sources and distribute hygiene kits, among other activities. 126,000 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 4 months.</narrative>
  </description>
